1.name: Strand of Hair
1.description: This could belong to anyone. Gross. Might make a good gift for those who groom...TOO much.

2.name: Dandelion Seed
2.description: This fluffy seed floats away when you blow on it. Makes adults feel like kids. Effect on kids unknown.

3.name: Spiderweb
3.description: Enemy of housekeepers who don't own ladders. BFF of Halloween enthusiasts. Good work, spiders.

4.name: Apple Core
4.description: Something happened here. Something...delicious. Oh well. Into the compost it goes.

5.name: Soda-Can Tab
5.description: Someone pulled this all the way off the can. Some people collect these to make necklaces. Pretty weird.

6.name: Empty Can
6.description: Great for playing Kick the Can, if you're absolutely, undeniably THAT bored. Please recycle it afterward!

7.name: Plastic Bag
7.description: You could use this for lots of stuff. Taking groceries to the car, taking them out of the car... Lots of stuff.

8.name: Shower Cap
8.description: Out of all the hats you could wear while taking a shower, this is the least stylish. Who would wear this?

9.name: Ribbon
9.description: Looks like someone untied this while opening a gift, then kept it for later. How practical!

10.name: Cashew
10.description: Great for a snack. It takes a lot of work to grow these nuts...but they taste really, really good.

11.name: Hard Candy
11.description: It's soda flavored. Ooh—and it's the kind that sparkles and fizzes on your tongue. That's the best kind!

12.name: Cracker
12.description: Can't party without one of these! Well, you could probably try, but...no one wants to be at that party.

13.name: Boiled Egg
13.description: Just an egg that's been boiled. Is that disappointing? Lower your expectations a bit. Thank you.

14.name: Scallion
14.description: You might call it a green onion, and you know what? That's fine. You do you.

15.name: Rubber Plug
15.description: A stopper for blocking drains in tubs. Without one of these, you'd have to bathe SUPER fast.

16.name: Light Bulb
16.description: A prop to hold above your head when you get a good idea. It also lights up, if you're into that.

17.name: Mystery Screw
17.description: Some machine must be rattling around without this. Hand it to a tinkerer, or toss it in a junk drawer.

18.name: Mystery Key
18.description: What does it unlock? A treasure chest? A footlocker full of smelly socks? The imagination reels...

19.name: Toilet Paper
19.description: A cherished tool. Whatever your troubles, if you have this handy, everything will work out in the end.

20.name: Toothbrush
20.description: Essential for good dental hygiene. You could also use one to scrub floors! Just...don't mix them up.

21.name: Milk
21.description: Nutrient-rich cow juice in a cute little bottle. Don't drink too much too fast. Your tummy will thank you.

22.name: Garlic
22.description: Powerful flavor, powerful stench. Makes a stellar seasoning but packs quite a punch. Hwoof!

23.name: Banana
23.description: A snack with appeal. Ugh. Sorry.

24.name: Grapes
24.description: It's some grapes! Everyone loves grapes. You love grapes too, right? Well, either way...it's some grapes.

25.name: Smoothie
25.description: One hundred percent pureed fruit. Perfect for those who love fruit flavors but hate using their teeth.

26.name: Meat Dumpling
26.description: It's a delicious-looking dumpling! Smells amazing. Mmm... Sorry, what were we talking about?

27.name: Ice Cream
27.description: As yummy as it is cold. Your taste buds will love you. Your sensitive chompers won't. Sorry, teeth.

28.name: Donut
28.description: The widely popular "pink with sprinkles" flavor. Worth waiting in line for...probably.

29.name: Floppy Disk
29.description: A storage device from an ancient time. Might contain some secrets...forbidden, teeny-tiny secrets.

30.name: Octopus Sausage
30.description: No bento box is complete without one of these. Mostly cute. Sort of creepy. All the way edible.

31.name: Pudding
31.description: A delightful, jiggly treat. It even has whipped cream on top! One wobbly bite and bliss will be yours.

32.name: Rose
32.description: A flower that can't NOT be tied to romance. Grip one in your teeth to look dashing—just mind the thorns.

33.name: Magnet
33.description: The letter U but used for science. Great for metal-based experiments or, more often, cartoon hijinks.

34.name: Paper Wrestler
34.description: A paper pugilist for rowdy youths. Drum on the table to engage your opponent! Weak to scissors.

35.name: Faucet Handle
35.description: Someone, somewhere is unable to wash their hands without this. Good as a spare part, perhaps.

36.name: Cake Roll
36.description: A log-shaped delight packed with fruit and frosting. Goes very well with tea.

37.name: Hamburger
37.description: A big, honkin' burger for a big, honkin' appetite. Go on—tear into it like no one's watching. Mmmm.

38.name: Pizza
38.description: Whoa! The cheese on top is extra gooey and delicious... So good! Is this from Mona Pizza?

39.name: Ramen
39.description: Broth, noodles, and happiness in a bowl. Great as a midnight snack. It's always midnight somewhere...

40.name: Japanese Curry
40.description: An all-time classic dish celebrated for its spiciness. It might give you rowdy guts, but it's soooo worth it.

41.name: Rubber Ducky
41.description: The king of the tub. A perfect little companion for animal lovers or die-hard bath enthusiasts.

42.name: Sock
42.description: Warm socks with Wario on them. His face warps when you put them on, but it still looks just like him.

43.name: Disguise Glasses
43.description: An incredible disguise that would fool anyone. Use them for daring heists...or to make people laugh.

44.name: Bicycle Pump
44.description: Push the thingy down to make air whoosh out of the little tube hole. That's called physics!

45.name: White Plate
45.description: It's...a regular plate. Nothing fancy. Perfect for anyone whose kids tend to break things...like plates.

46.name: Eye-Exam Stick
46.description: Covers one eye as you read letters out loud. Call it an "eye occluder" to hear people say, "Huh?"

47.name: Mustache Catalog
47.description: A respected periodical among facial-hair aficionados. Use it to brush up on 'stache fashion.

48.name: Piggy Bank
48.description: Feels heavy. Could be stuffed with coins and cash...but that widdle face is too cute to smash open.

49.name: Cactus
49.description: A prickly plant stuck mid-shrug. It's OK, buddy. No one expects you to have all the answers.

50.name: Sunglasses
50.description: An extra-chic design. Place them over your eyes to defeat the sun. Your move, space.

51.name: Matryoshka Doll
51.description: A doll within a doll. Within a doll. Within another doll. How many dolls are hiding in here?!

52.name: Hunk of Meat
52.description: Savory meat in its most ideal form. A perfect meal for boosting one's martial-arts training.

53.name: Bowling Pin
53.description: A pesky upstart who likes to ruin bowling scores. It kinda looks like an alien if you squint.

54.name: Soccer Ball
54.description: A sporty, speckled ball that's fun to kick. You might call it a football, and hey—that's perfectly fine.

55.name: Rugby Ball
55.description: Found rocketing between bruised, flailing sportsmen. An ideal gift for fans of both sports and flailing.

56.name: Birthday Cake
56.description: Happy birthday! We're so glad you're here.

57.name: Manhole Cover
57.description: This Wario-branded treasure has many uses other than covering manholes. Such as...well, many!

58.name: Afternoon Tea
58.description: A must-have for super-classy folks. All you need is some of those tiny sandwiches and teensy cakes.

59.name: Mushroom
59.description: Mmm, nothing says decadence like a smelly mushroom. You can smell it, can't you? CAN'T YOU?!

60.name: Sushi
60.description: A delicacy that pairs well with celebrations. Sushi lovers can't get enough of this stuff.

61.name: Marbled Meat
61.description: Stare at the marbling long enough and it'll start to look like art. A fave of foodies and pooches alike.

62.name: High-Tech Shoes
62.description: These kicks are slick, and they fit you perfectly. With these, no racing dream is out of reach.

63.name: Headphones
63.description: A pricey gadget for audiophiles. Can you hear the difference? Pfft, of course you can.

64.name: Boxing Glove
64.description: A boxing champ is nothing without a pair of these. Sweat stains only increase their value.

65.name: Bat
65.description: The smell of the wood transports you back in time. Why am I sniffing a bat? Sheesh, don't be so judgy!

66.name: Dumbbell
66.description: Lift, and then lift again. Switch sides and repeat ad infinitum. Such is the formula for greatness!

67.name: Electric Fan
67.description: Talk into it to sound like a robot. Oh, it also cools the room, or whatever.

68.name: Rafflesia
68.description: This is one profoundly pungent flower. A great decoration option for those who hate company.

69.name: Mobile Phone
69.description: An ancient device used in ancient times for communication. It flips closed. What. Even.

70.name: Digital Camera
70.description: A machine that captures memories on shiny memory paper. What is this sorcery?!

71.name: Electric Guitar
71.description: Just hold this and, blammo, you're cool. Just like that. I think it also makes music.

72.name: Dual-Sport Bicycle
72.description: A sleek yet practical device. Why walk when you can run? Why run when you can bike?

73.name: Laptop
73.description: A compact, slim design for adults who work on the go but hate carrying heavy stuff.

74.name: Deer Scare
74.description: A tool that keeps doe-linquents at arm's length. Terrifying for them. Soothing and zen-like for humans.

75.name: Wedding Dress
75.description: This dress represents the dream of happily ever after. Do not, I repeat, DO NOT spill on it.

76.name: Alpenhorn
76.description: This instrument brings to mind mountaintops. Yodel-ay-hee-who wouldn't want in on this?

77.name: Haniwa Figure
77.description: That expression says it all. These things are especially popular with the ladies.

78.name: Super-Fancy Toilet
78.description: This primo toilet is gentle on the bottom, though it may take some getting used to.

79.name: Tuna
79.description: You can tune a piano, but you can't tuna fish. Until now! That's called beating a system.

80.name: Mandrake Root
80.description: It's a plant...right? Wait, it's staring at me. That's super not normal for a plant.

81.name: Body-Builder Statue
81.description: A statue of a buff and hunky Wario. In other words, a statue of Wario. Tear your eyes away...if you can.

82.name: Minitruck
82.description: This thing is both useful and fun to drive. Hop in, and take a whirl around the countryside.

83.name: Expensive Vase
83.description: Break this and it's over. What's over? You don't even want to know. Just don't break it, OK?

84.name: Painting
84.description: This exquisite piece is the only art you or the world will even need. If you lack taste, the exit's that way.

85.name: Gold Card
85.description: A card that can make all of your wishes come true. If you're not overtly greedy, it's just a card.

86.name: Golden Egg
86.description: It's empty, so don't expect a golden gosling or anything. It is exceptionally round.

87.name: Red Gem
87.description: A huge, bright-red jewel. Some people find the way it twinkles rather enchanting.

88.name: Cabin Cruiser
88.description: Slices through the waves like a knife through so much butter. Live it up, why don't you?

89.name: Helicopter
89.description: This chopper is proper, but its propeller is sweller.

90.name: Large-Scale Crane
90.description: It's called a crane because kids crane their necks to get a gander. I didn't make that up, really.

91.name: Gaudy Crown
91.description: A real head turner. Great for folks with a take-charge attitude.

92.name: Golden Toilet
92.description: A toilet made of gold. Even your booty deserves the life of luxury.

93.name: Company Building
93.description: Your very own office building. If you want a whole floor dedicated to garlic, that's your call.

94.name: Golf Course
94.description: A paradise for golfers. A gold mine for landscapers. Just an empty field for the rest of us.

95.name: Desert Island
95.description: A lovely island full of plants and animals and the like. For the person who has everything.

96.name: Luxury Cruise Ship
96.description: Maybe no one knows how famous you are yet, but that doesn't mean you can't party it up like a celeb.

97.name: Jumbo Jet
97.description: A jumbo jet for those with jumbo travel needs. Steer clear if you're afraid of heights.

98.name: Tigronic Model
98.description: GASP. It's a crime-fighting, super-duper robot friend! Who doesn't love these things?

99.name: Spaceship
99.description: The latest and greatest in space travel. The cosmos is your personal playground with this.

100.name: Giant Meteorite
100.description: It's giant! Enormous! Ginormous, even! Don't run into it because, you know, just don't.
